# Testing Rules — aide

## Pyramid

- Many unit tests — fast, isolated
- Some integration tests — API and DB boundaries
- Few e2e tests — critical user journeys only

## Unit Tests

- Test behavior, not implementation details
- One assertion focus per test when practical
- Mock external dependencies at infrastructure boundary

## Integration Tests

- Use test database or containers — never production
- Reset state between tests
- Cover happy path and primary error paths

## E2E Tests

- Cover P0 user flows from `docs/project.md`
- Stable selectors — data-testid preferred
- No flaky waits — use deterministic conditions

## Coverage

- Business logic in domain layer must have unit tests
- New bugs require regression test before fix merge

## Prohibited

- Deleting or skipping tests to pass CI
- Tests that depend on execution order
- Hard-coded production URLs in test config
